  09 Jan 2004; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> ruby-libglade-0.30.ebuild:
  stable on alpha

*ruby-libglade-0.34 (05 Aug 2003)

  05 Aug 2003; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> ruby-libglade-0.34.ebuild:
  Update to current release

  05 Aug 2003; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> ruby-libglade-0.30.ebuild:
  Make this depend on the pre-2.0 versions of libglade to fix bug 22027

*ruby-libglade-0.30 (07 Jan 2003)

	07 Jan 2003; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> ruby-libglade-0.30.ebuild:
	Update from 0.29 to 0.30.  Add ~alpha to KEYWORDS.

*ruby-libglade-0.29 (06 Jul 2002)

	06 Jul 2002: Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> ruby-libglade-0.29.ebuild:

	Version 0.29 is NEWER than 1.2 because it changed maintainership and was
	rolled into the ruby-gnome package.  ruby-libglade-1.2 should never have
	been put into Gentoo, though that wasn't obvious from the version numbers.
	Added SLOT and LICENSE.

	07 Jul 2002: Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> ruby-libglade-0.29.ebuild:

	Added KEYWORDS.

*ruby-libglade-1.2 (27 May 2002)

	27 May 2002; Seemant Kulleen <seemant@gentoo.org> ruby-libglade-1.2.ebuild
	files/digest-ruby-libglade-1.2 :

	ekarttun@cs.helsinki.fi (Einar Karttunen) submitted this much needed
	update in bug #1258.  This version of the package is not a ruby-gnome
	package, but actually a ruby-libglade package.

	07 Jul 2002; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> ruby-libglade-1.2.ebuild:

	Added LICENSE, KEYWORDS, SLOT.

*ruby-libglade-0.27

	07 Jul 2002; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> ruby-libglade-0.27.ebuild:

	Added LICENSE, KEYWORDS, SLOT.
